diff --git a/product/ACCEPTANCE-CRITERIA.md b/product/ACCEPTANCE-CRITERIA.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..0433219
--- /dev/null
+++ b/product/ACCEPTANCE-CRITERIA.md
@@ -0,0 +1,76 @@
+# Product acceptance criteria
+
+## Public authority
+
+- Every published legal proposition has a review date and inspectable source basis.
+- Source type and authority hierarchy are visible.
+- Effective dates and jurisdiction scope are explicit.
+- Public pages disclose educational-information limitations.
+- Existing high-value URLs have tested redirects or preservation plans.
+
+## Change intelligence
+
+- A change record identifies the changed rule version and delta.
+- Materiality includes a rationale and portfolio denominator.
+- Likely reach is distinguishable from resolved reach.
+- Open facts and source gaps are visible.
+- The record can open or update a governed matter.
+
+## Applicability
+
+- An evaluation records rule, engine, and fact-snapshot versions.
+- Every failed or unresolved predicate is inspectable.
+- Property and workforce facts have owners, sources, and freshness.
+- No material missing fact is silently assumed.
+
+## Matters
+
+- Scope, owner, lifecycle, privilege, and next action are explicit.
+- Findings separate law, fact, computation, judgment, and limitation.
+- Scenarios retain inputs, assumptions, and model versions.
+- Actions and controls link to findings.
+- Closure criteria and revalidation triggers are defined.
+
+## Controls and evidence
+
+- Every control links to an obligation or finding.
+- Operation and assurance ownership are distinct where required.
+- Cadence, population, evidence, and test method are specified.
+- Exceptions are tracked through remediation or acceptance.
+- Evidence integrity and retention metadata are preserved.
+
+## Decision records
+
+- The decision request is unambiguous.
+- Recommendation, alternatives, consequences, and conditions are present.
+- Approvers and timestamps are immutable.
+- The approved provenance snapshot is preserved.
+- Dependency changes create a revalidation state rather than mutating history.
+
+## Security and privacy
+
+- Every private request is tenant- and permission-scoped server-side.
+- Public and private retrieval contexts cannot bleed into one another.
+- Privileged matters support restricted search and export.
+- Employee data is minimized and access-logged.
+- Audit events cover material reads, changes, exports, approvals, and AI use.
+
+## Accessibility and quality
+
+- WCAG 2.2 AA target with automated and manual testing.
+- Keyboard navigation and visible focus for every interactive control.
+- No document-level horizontal overflow at supported viewports.
+- Dense tables and matrices remain bounded and scrollable.
+- Core workflows work without browser-console errors.
+- Performance budgets are established for public and enterprise routes.
+
+## Prototype repository
+
+- deterministic build
+- complete route manifest
+- internal-link validation
+- data-integrity tests
+- responsive browser QA
+- interaction acceptance tests
+- GitHub Pages build path
+- documented production boundary
diff --git a/product/ADRS/0001-governed-object-graph.md b/product/ADRS/0001-governed-object-graph.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..1890dcc
--- /dev/null
+++ b/product/ADRS/0001-governed-object-graph.md
@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@
+# ADR 0001 — Governed object graph over page-centric architecture
+
+**Status:** Accepted for v2 prototype
+
+## Decision
+
+Model legal intelligence and enterprise response as versioned, linked entities. Pages and reports are projections of those entities.
+
+## Rationale
+
+A page-centric architecture duplicates facts, permits drift, and makes downstream invalidation difficult. The product’s differentiator depends on causal continuity from authority to response evidence.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- more up-front schema and governance work
+- stable IDs and versioning required
+- content authors and rule engineers work against explicit contracts
+- executive artifacts can be regenerated without losing provenance
+- dependency changes can trigger targeted revalidation
